Package org.ejbca.ui.web.pub

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ApplyBean
    A class used as an interface between Apply jsp pages and ejbca functions.
    AutoEnrollServlet
    Parses a posted request and returns a correct certificate depending on the type.
    CertDistServlet
    Servlet used to distribute certificates and CRLs.
    The servlet is called with method GET or POST and syntax command=<command>.
    CertReqServlet
    Servlet used to install a private key with a corresponding certificate in a browser.
    ClearCacheServlet
    Servlet used to clear all caches (Global Configuration Cache, End Entity Profile Cache, Certificate Profile Cache, Log Configuration Cache, Authorization Cache and CA Cache).
    DemoCertReqServlet
    This is a servlet that is used for creating a user into EJBCA and retrieving her certificate.
    HealthCheckServlet
    Servlet used to check the health of an EJBCA instance and can be used to build a cluster using a loadbalancer.
    MSCertTools  
    NoCacheFilter
    Filter that prevents a browser to cache everything except resources like java script, css and images.
    RegisterReqBean
    Used by enrol/reg*.jsp for self-registration.
    RegisterReqBean.TokenTypeInfo  
    RequestInstance  
    SameRequestRateLimiter<T>
    Helper class for use when multiple threads a requesting something that will end up with the same result.
    ServletDebug
    Prints debug info back to browser client
    ServletUtils
    A class containing some helpful functions used in more than one Servlet, avoiding code duplication.
